    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "ABOUT SUNO\n\nWe're building the world's first platform for creating and discovering original music, including Suno Studio, a generative audio workstation, and Hooks, a new way to create and share videos that bring songs to life.\n\nPowered by the leading music-creation model and designed to amplify imagination, our platform makes it possible for anyone to turn inspiration into music. With Suno, ideas flow into sound, songs become yours, and everyone can experience the joy of creating.\n\n\nSuno is one of the fastest-growing AI startups in the world, backed by leading investors including Menlo Ventures, Lightspeed Venture Partners, Matrix, NVentures, and Hallwood Media.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nIf you’re the kind of engineering leader who’d rather ship than spectate, this one’s for you. You’ll lead a team building core product and platform capabilities for over 100 million creators — shaping system design, driving execution, and partnering with product, design, and data science to deliver experiences people actually love. This is a hands-on leadership role: you’ll set technical direction, grow your team, and keep things moving in a fast-paced, music-obsessed environment.\n\nCheck out the Suno version of this role here! https://suno.com/s/H3GzRpa6Ze9A6DKr\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Own the technical direction for your team’s domain, driving architecture decisions and ensuring scalable, high-quality systems that serve millions of creators\n\n - Build, coach, and grow a team of engineers — hiring strong talent, running effective performance cycles, and creating a culture where people do their best work\n\n - Partner with product management, design, and data science to define roadmaps, scope projects, and ship features that move the needle\n\n - Navigate the full development lifecycle from ideation through launch, managing tradeoffs and removing blockers so your team stays focused and shipping\n\n - Champion engineering craft across your team — code quality, robust testing, and the right balance of rapid iteration with long-term maintainability\n\n - Contribute to Suno’s mission of making creative fulfillment a daily reality for everyone by delivering the tools and platform that turn imagination into music\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED\n\nMust-Haves\n\n - 5–7 years managing a software engineering team, with a track record of shipping impactful consumer products\n\n - Strong technical foundation — you can review code, guide architectural decisions, and jump into the codebase when needed\n\n - Experience translating ambiguous problems into clear plans and shipped features alongside product, design, and data science partners\n\n - A demonstrated ability to hire, develop, and retain strong engineers — you care deeply about growing people’s careers\n\n - Hands-on experience building and operating systems at scale in a production environment\n\n - Comfort thriving in fast-paced, ambiguous environments while keeping your team focused across multiple priorities\n\n - Forward-looking perspective on integrating AI and agentic coding into production engineering workflows\n\n - A love of music (listening, exploring, making — we’re not picky about genre)\n\nNice-to-Haves\n\n - Experience at a consumer tech or creator-platform company\n\n - Time spent at both larger organizations and smaller, high-growth startups\n\n - Familiarity with AI/ML-powered product development\n\n - Working knowledge of Python, TypeScript, consumer media systems, or real-time systems\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Notes:\n\n - Applicants must be eligible to work in the U.S\n\n - This is an in-person role based in Suno’s Cambridge office\n\n\nPERKS \u0026 BENEFITS\n\n - Company equity package\n\n - 401(k) with 3% employer match (includes Roth 401(k))\n\n - Medical, dental, and vision insurance (PPO with HSA \u0026 FSA options)\n\n - 11 paid holidays + unlimited PTO and sick time\n\n - 16 weeks of paid parental leave\n\n - Generous commuter benefit\n\n - Creative education stipend\n\nSuno is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We consider qualified applicants without regard to race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, marital or family status, disability, genetic information, veteran status, or any other legally protected basis under provincial, federal, state, and local laws, regulations, or ordinances. We will also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the requirements of state and local laws, including the Massachusetts Fair Chance in Employment Act, NYC Fair Chance Act, LA City Fair Chance Ordinance, and San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
